searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Builder","doc":"Declarative PDF builder from template lists.\n\nRenders a list of content tuples into a PDF document, applying\nglobal configuration for page size, margins, fonts, and templates.","ref":"Pdf.Builder.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Pdf.Builder","doc":"template = [\n      {:text, \"Title\", %{font_size: 24, bold: true}},\n      {:spacer, 10},\n      {:text, \"Body text\", %{font_size: 12}},\n      {:line, %{color: :gray}},\n      {:page_break},\n      {:text, \"Page 2\", %{font_size: 18}}\n    ]\n\n    config = %{\n      size: :a4,\n      margin: 40,\n      font: \"Helvetica\",\n      font_size: 12\n    }\n\n    doc = Pdf.Builder.render(template, config)\n    binary = Pdf.export(doc)","ref":"Pdf.Builder.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Builder.render/2","doc":"Render a template list with the given config into a PDF document.","ref":"Pdf.Builder.html#render/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Config keys - Pdf.Builder.render/2","doc":"- `:size` — page size (default `:a4`)\n- `:margin` — margin value or map (default `0`)\n- `:font` — default font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — default font size (default `12`)\n- `:compress` — compress streams (default `true`)\n- `:header` — `fn doc, page_info -> doc end` template\n- `:footer` — `fn doc, page_info -> doc end` template\n- `:watermark` — `fn doc, page_info -> doc end` template\n- `:background` — `fn doc, page_info -> doc end` template","ref":"Pdf.Builder.html#render/2-config-keys"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Builder.render_into/2","doc":"Render a template list into an existing document.\nNested lists are automatically flattened.","ref":"Pdf.Builder.html#render_into/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Alert","doc":"Alert/Callout component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a colored notification box with an icon character, title,\nand message text. Supports info, warning, error, and success variants.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Alert.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Alert","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.Alert.render({50, 700}, %{\n      type: :info,\n      title: \"Note\",\n      message: \"This is an informational message.\",\n      width: 400\n    })\n\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Alert.render({50, 700}, %{\n      type: :error,\n      title: \"Error\",\n      message: \"Something went wrong. Please try again.\",\n      width: 400\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Alert.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Alert.render/3","doc":"Render an alert at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Alert.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Alert.render/3","doc":"- `:type` — `:info` (default), `:success`, `:warning`, or `:error`\n- `:title` — bold title text\n- `:message` — body message text (required)\n- `:width` — alert width (required)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:padding` — inner padding (default `12`)\n- `:border_radius` — corner radius (default `5`)\n- `:icon` — override icon character","ref":"Pdf.Component.Alert.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Avatar","doc":"Avatar component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a circular (or rounded) container with an image or initials,\nwith optional border and elevation (box-shadow simulation).\n\nInspired by Material UI's Avatar component.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Avatar.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Avatar","doc":"# Avatar with initials\n    doc\n    |> Pdf.Component.Avatar.render({100, 700}, %{\n      size: 48,\n      initials: \"AM\",\n      background: {0.3, 0.5, 0.9},\n      color: :white,\n      elevation: 2\n    })\n\n    # Avatar with image\n    doc\n    |> Pdf.Component.Avatar.render({200, 700}, %{\n      size: 64,\n      image: \"path/to/photo.jpg\",\n      border: 2,\n      border_color: :white,\n      elevation: 3\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Avatar.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Avatar.render/3","doc":"Render an avatar at `{x, y}` (top-left corner).","ref":"Pdf.Component.Avatar.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Avatar.render/3","doc":"- `:size` — single number or `{width, height}` tuple in points (default `40`)\n- `:initials` — 1-3 character string to display (default `nil`)\n- `:image` — path to JPEG/PNG image or `{:binary, data}` (default `nil`)\n- `:background` — fill color behind initials (default gray)\n- `:color` — text color for initials (default white)\n- `:font` — font name for initials (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:border` — border width (default `0`)\n- `:border_color` — border color (default `:black`)\n- `:border_radius` — `:circle` (default), `:rounded`, or number\n- `:elevation` — shadow level 0-5, like Material UI (default `0`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Avatar.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Badge","doc":"Badge component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a small circle or pill-shaped label, typically used to show\ncounts, notifications, or status indicators overlaid on another element.\n\nInspired by Material UI's Badge component.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Badge.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Badge","doc":"# Simple notification badge\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Badge.render({120, 710}, %{content: \"3\"})\n\n    # Custom styled badge\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Badge.render({200, 700}, %{\n      content: \"NEW\",\n      background: {0.18, 0.72, 0.45},\n      color: :white,\n      variant: :pill\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Badge.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Badge.render/3","doc":"Render a badge at `{x, y}` (center point).","ref":"Pdf.Component.Badge.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Badge.render/3","doc":"- `:content` — text to display (default `\"\"`)\n- `:background` — fill color (default red)\n- `:color` — text color (default white)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — font size (default `8`)\n- `:size` — diameter for dot/circle variant (default `18`)\n- `:variant` — `:dot` (no text), `:standard` (circle), or `:pill` (auto-width)\n- `:border` — border width (default `0`)\n- `:border_color` — border color (default `:white`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Badge.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Barcode","doc":"Barcode PDF component — renders Code 128 barcodes onto a PDF.\n\nThis is a **thin renderer**. All encoding logic (standard and shaped)\nlives in `ex_barcode`. This component only scales and draws.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Standard barcode - Pdf.Component.Barcode","doc":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.render(doc, {50, 700}, %{data: \"ABC-12345\", width: 200})","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html#module-standard-barcode"},{"type":"module","title":"Shape barcode (creative barcode with silhouette + decorations) - Pdf.Component.Barcode","doc":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.render(doc, {50, 700}, %{\n      data: \"DEMOCAMP\", width: 250, height: 100, shape: :rv\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html#module-shape-barcode-creative-barcode-with-silhouette-decorations"},{"type":"module","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Barcode","doc":"","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html#module-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Core - Pdf.Component.Barcode","doc":"- `:data` — the string to encode (required)\n  - `:width` — barcode width in points (default `200`)\n  - `:height` — bar height in points (default `50`, or auto from aspect ratio)\n  - `:color` — bar color (default `{0, 0, 0}`)\n  - `:background` — optional background color (standard barcodes only)\n  - `:quiet_zone` — modules of white space (default `10` standard, `2` shaped)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html#module-core"},{"type":"module","title":"Text - Pdf.Component.Barcode","doc":"- `:show_text` — render data below bars (default `true`)\n  - `:font` / `:font_size` / `:text_color` — text styling\n  - `:label` — optional title above barcode\n  - `:label_font_size` / `:label_color` — label styling","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html#module-text"},{"type":"module","title":"Image - Pdf.Component.Barcode","doc":"- `:image` — path, URL, or `{:binary, data}`\n  - `:image_size` — `{w, h}` (default `{40, 40}`)\n  - `:image_position` — `:left`, `:right`, `:top` (default `:left`)\n  - `:image_gap` — gap between image and barcode (default `8`)\n  - `:image_border_radius` — rounded clip (default `0`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html#module-image"},{"type":"module","title":"Shape (delegated to ExBarcode.Shape) - Pdf.Component.Barcode","doc":"- `:shape` — predefined shape: `:rv`, `:camper`, `:city`, `:wave`, `:diamond`, `:hill`\n  - `:contour_top` — custom top contour `[{x_pct, y_pct}, ...]`\n  - `:contour_bottom` — custom bottom contour\n  - `:bar_min_height` — minimum bar fraction (default `0.0`)\n  - `:decoration_color` — color for decorations (default same as `:color`)\n  - `:decoration_stroke_color` — stroke color for stroke decorations (default lighter)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html#module-shape-delegated-to-exbarcode-shape"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.render/3","doc":"","ref":"Pdf.Component.Barcode.html#render/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Blockquote","doc":"Blockquote component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders an indented text block with a colored left bar,\noptional background, and citation line.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Blockquote.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Blockquote","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.Blockquote.render({50, 700}, %{width: 400},\n      \"The best way to predict the future is to invent it.\")\n\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Blockquote.render({50, 700}, %{\n      width: 400,\n      bar_color: {0.2, 0.5, 0.8},\n      cite: \"— Alan Kay\"\n    }, \"The best way to predict the future is to invent it.\")","ref":"Pdf.Component.Blockquote.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Blockquote.render/4","doc":"Render a blockquote at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Blockquote.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Blockquote.render/4","doc":"- `:width` — total width of the blockquote (required)\n- `:bar_color` — left accent bar color (default gray)\n- `:bar_width` — bar thickness (default `3`)\n- `:background` — optional background color\n- `:padding` — inner padding (default `12`)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — text size (default `10`)\n- `:color` — text color (default dark gray)\n- `:italic` — render text in italic (default `true`)\n- `:cite` — optional citation line below the quote\n- `:cite_color` — citation text color (default lighter gray)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Blockquote.html#render/4-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Card","doc":"Card component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a container with optional header, body, and footer sections,\nelevation (box-shadow), and rounded corners. Designed for structured\ncontent blocks like profile cards, info panels, and summaries.\n\nInspired by Material UI's Card component.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Card.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Card","doc":"# Simple card with callback\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Card.render({50, 700}, {300, 150}, %{\n      elevation: 2,\n      border_radius: 8\n    }, fn doc, area ->\n      doc |> Pdf.text_at({area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Card content\")\n    end)\n\n    # Card with header and body\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Card.render({50, 700}, {300, 200}, %{\n      elevation: 3,\n      header: %{title: \"User Profile\", subtitle: \"Senior Developer\"},\n      padding: 12\n    }, fn doc, area ->\n      doc |> Pdf.text_at({area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Card body content here\")\n    end)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Card.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Card.render/5","doc":"Render a card at `{x, y}` (top-left) with size `{w, h}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Card.html#render/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Card.render/5","doc":"- `:background` — card background color (default white)\n- `:border_radius` — corner radius (default `8`)\n- `:border` — border width (default `0`)\n- `:border_color` — border color (default light gray)\n- `:elevation` — shadow level 0-5 (default `1`)\n- `:padding` — inner padding (default `12`)\n- `:header` — map with `:title`, `:subtitle`, `:background`, `:height`\n- `:footer` — map with `:text`, `:background`, `:height`\n\nThe callback receives `fn doc, area -> ... end` where `area` is the\ncontent area after header and padding are accounted for.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Card.html#render/5-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Chart","doc":"Chart component for PDF documents — renders bar, line, and pie charts.\n\nAll charts are rendered using PDF drawing primitives (rectangles, lines,\narcs) with no external dependencies.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Bar chart - Pdf.Component.Chart","doc":"Pdf.Component.Chart.bar_chart(doc, {50, 500}, %{\n      width: 300, height: 200,\n      data: [\n        %{label: \"Q1\", value: 120, color: {0.2, 0.6, 0.9}},\n        %{label: \"Q2\", value: 180, color: {0.9, 0.4, 0.2}},\n        %{label: \"Q3\", value: 95,  color: {0.3, 0.8, 0.4}},\n        %{label: \"Q4\", value: 210, color: {0.8, 0.2, 0.5}}\n      ],\n      title: \"Quarterly Revenue\"\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#module-bar-chart"},{"type":"module","title":"Line chart - Pdf.Component.Chart","doc":"Pdf.Component.Chart.line_chart(doc, {50, 500}, %{\n      width: 300, height: 200,\n      series: [\n        %{label: \"Sales\",    values: [10, 25, 18, 42, 35], color: {0.2, 0.5, 0.9}},\n        %{label: \"Expenses\", values: [8, 15, 22, 30, 28],  color: {0.9, 0.3, 0.3}}\n      ],\n      x_labels: [\"Jan\", \"Feb\", \"Mar\", \"Apr\", \"May\"],\n      title: \"Monthly Trend\"\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#module-line-chart"},{"type":"module","title":"Pie chart - Pdf.Component.Chart","doc":"Pdf.Component.Chart.pie_chart(doc, {50, 500}, %{\n      radius: 80,\n      data: [\n        %{label: \"Mobile\",  value: 45, color: {0.2, 0.6, 0.9}},\n        %{label: \"Desktop\", value: 35, color: {0.9, 0.4, 0.2}},\n        %{label: \"Tablet\",  value: 20, color: {0.3, 0.8, 0.4}}\n      ],\n      title: \"Device Distribution\"\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#module-pie-chart"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Chart.bar_chart/3","doc":"Render a vertical bar chart.\n\n`{x, y}` is the top-left corner of the chart area.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#bar_chart/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Chart.bar_chart/3","doc":"- `:data` — list of `%{label: str, value: number}` (required)\n- `:width` / `:height` — chart dimensions (default `300` × `200`)\n- `:title` — optional title above chart\n- `:show_values` — display value on top of each bar (default `true`)\n- `:show_grid` — horizontal grid lines (default `true`)\n- `:grid_lines` — number of grid lines (default `5`)\n- `:bar_gap` — fraction of bar width used as gap (default `0.3`)\n- `:bar_radius` — top corner radius (default `0`)\n- `:colors` — list of colors to cycle through\n- `:axis_color` / `:grid_color` / `:text_color`","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#bar_chart/3-style-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Chart.horizontal_bar_chart/3","doc":"Render a horizontal bar chart — useful for ranking or comparison data.\n\n`{x, y}` is the top-left corner.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#horizontal_bar_chart/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Chart.horizontal_bar_chart/3","doc":"Same as `bar_chart/3` but bars grow left-to-right.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#horizontal_bar_chart/3-style-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Chart.line_chart/3","doc":"Render a line chart with one or more series.\n\n`{x, y}` is the top-left corner.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#line_chart/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Chart.line_chart/3","doc":"- `:series` — list of `%{label: str, values: [number], color: color}` (required)\n- `:x_labels` — labels for the x-axis points\n- `:width` / `:height` — chart dimensions (default `300` × `200`)\n- `:title` — optional title\n- `:show_dots` — render dots at data points (default `true`)\n- `:show_grid` — horizontal grid lines (default `true`)\n- `:grid_lines` — number of grid lines (default `5`)\n- `:dot_radius` — radius of data point dots (default `2.5`)\n- `:line_width` — stroke width for lines (default `1.5`)\n- `:show_legend` — show legend below chart (default `true`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#line_chart/3-style-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Chart.pie_chart/3","doc":"Render a pie chart.\n\n`{x, y}` is the center of the pie.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#pie_chart/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Chart.pie_chart/3","doc":"- `:data` — list of `%{label: str, value: number}` (required)\n- `:radius` — pie radius (default `80`)\n- `:title` — optional title above\n- `:donut` — inner radius fraction for donut chart (default `0`, set to `0.5` for donut)\n- `:show_labels` — draw labels with lines (default `true`)\n- `:show_percentages` — show % in labels (default `true`)\n- `:colors` — color cycle","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chart.html#pie_chart/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Chip","doc":"Chip component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a compact rounded label/tag element, useful for displaying\ncategories, tags, status indicators, or filter selections.\n\nInspired by Material UI's Chip component.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chip.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Chip","doc":"# Simple chip\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Chip.render({50, 400}, %{label: \"Elixir\"})\n\n    # Outlined chip\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Chip.render({50, 400}, %{\n      label: \"Active\",\n      variant: :outlined,\n      color: {0.18, 0.72, 0.45}\n    })\n\n    # Filled chip with custom colors\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Chip.render({50, 400}, %{\n      label: \"Priority\",\n      background: {0.85, 0.26, 0.33},\n      color: :white\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chip.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Chip.render/3","doc":"Render a chip at `{x, y}` (top-left corner).\n\nReturns `{doc, width}` — the document and the rendered chip width.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chip.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Chip.render/3","doc":"- `:label` — text to display (required)\n- `:variant` — `:filled` (default) or `:outlined`\n- `:background` — fill color for filled variant (default light gray)\n- `:color` — text/border color (default dark gray)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — font size (default `10`)\n- `:height` — chip height in points (default `24`)\n- `:padding_h` — horizontal padding (default `10`)\n- `:border` — border width for outlined variant (default `1`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Chip.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.CodeBlock","doc":"Code block component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders monospaced text with a background box, optional line numbers,\nand syntax-like styling. Designed for code snippets and terminal output.","ref":"Pdf.Component.CodeBlock.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.CodeBlock","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.CodeBlock.render({50, 700}, %{width: 400},\n      \"defmodule Hello do\\n  def world, do: :ok\\nend\")\n\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.CodeBlock.render({50, 700}, %{\n      width: 400,\n      line_numbers: true,\n      background: {0.15, 0.15, 0.18}\n      color: {0.9, 0.9, 0.9}\n    }, code)","ref":"Pdf.Component.CodeBlock.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.CodeBlock.render/4","doc":"Render a code block at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.CodeBlock.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.CodeBlock.render/4","doc":"- `:width` — block width (required)\n- `:font` — monospaced font (default `\"Courier\"`)\n- `:font_size` — text size (default `9`)\n- `:color` — text color (default dark)\n- `:background` — background color (default light gray)\n- `:border_color` — border color (default gray)\n- `:border_radius` — corner radius (default `4`)\n- `:padding` — inner padding (default `10`)\n- `:line_height` — spacing between lines (default `13`)\n- `:line_numbers` — show line numbers (default `false`)\n- `:line_number_color` — line number color (default muted)\n- `:title` — optional title/filename above the block","ref":"Pdf.Component.CodeBlock.html#render/4-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Divider","doc":"Divider component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a horizontal or vertical line separator with configurable\ncolor, width, style (solid/dashed), and margin.\n\nInspired by Material UI's Divider component.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Divider.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Divider","doc":"# Simple horizontal divider\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Divider.render({50, 400}, %{width: 200})\n\n    # Dashed divider with color\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Divider.render({50, 400}, %{\n      width: 200,\n      color: {0.8, 0.8, 0.8},\n      style: :dashed,\n      thickness: 0.5\n    })\n\n    # Vertical divider\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Divider.render({250, 700}, %{\n      height: 100,\n      orientation: :vertical\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Divider.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Divider.render/3","doc":"Render a divider at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Divider.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Divider.render/3","doc":"- `:width` — length for horizontal dividers (default `0`, required for horizontal)\n- `:height` — length for vertical dividers (default `0`, required for vertical)\n- `:orientation` — `:horizontal` (default) or `:vertical`\n- `:color` — line color (default light gray)\n- `:thickness` — line width in points (default `0.5`)\n- `:style` — `:solid` (default) or `:dashed`\n- `:dash` — custom dash pattern `{on, off}` (default `{3, 3}`)\n- `:margin_top` — space above (default `0`)\n- `:margin_bottom` — space below (default `0`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Divider.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Footnote","doc":"Footnote component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders footnotes at a given position with a separator line,\nsuperscript numbers, and smaller text.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Footnote.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Footnote","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.Footnote.render({50, 100}, %{width: 450}, [\n      \"Source: World Bank Data, 2025\",\n      \"All figures adjusted for inflation\",\n      \"Excluding outlier regions\"\n    ])","ref":"Pdf.Component.Footnote.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Footnote.render/4","doc":"Render footnotes at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Footnote.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Footnote.render/4","doc":"- `:width` — available width (default `450`)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — text size (default `7`)\n- `:color` — text color\n- `:line_color` — separator line color\n- `:line_height` — spacing between notes (default `11`)\n- `:separator_width` — width of the top separator line (default `80`)\n- `:start_number` — first footnote number (default `1`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Footnote.html#render/4-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.KeyValue","doc":"Key-value pair component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders aligned label-value rows, like invoice details or profile info.","ref":"Pdf.Component.KeyValue.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.KeyValue","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.KeyValue.render({50, 700}, %{width: 300}, [\n      {\"Name:\", \"John Doe\"},\n      {\"Email:\", \"john@example.com\"},\n      {\"Role:\", \"Admin\"}\n    ])","ref":"Pdf.Component.KeyValue.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.KeyValue.measure_height/2","doc":"Calculate the total height this key-value list will occupy,\naccounting for word-wrap on long values.\n\nTakes the same `style` map as `render/4` plus the `pairs` list.\nReturns the height in points.","ref":"Pdf.Component.KeyValue.html#measure_height/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.KeyValue.render/4","doc":"Render key-value pairs at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.KeyValue.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.KeyValue.render/4","doc":"- `:width` — total width (default `300`)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — text size (default `10`)\n- `:label_color` — label text color\n- `:value_color` — value text color\n- `:line_height` — row spacing (default `18`)\n- `:label_width` — fraction of width for labels (default `0.35`)\n- `:divider` — show divider between rows (default `false`)\n- `:divider_color` — divider line color\n- `:striped` — alternate row backgrounds (default `false`)\n- `:stripe_color` — background for even rows\n- `:value_align` — `:left` (default) or `:right` to right-align values\n- `:label_bold` — bold labels (default `true`)\n- `:value_bold` — bold values (default `false`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.KeyValue.html#render/4-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.List","doc":"List component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders bulleted or numbered lists with support for nesting,\ncustom markers, and per-level styling.","ref":"Pdf.Component.List.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.List","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.List.render({50, 700}, %{}, [\n      \"First item\",\n      \"Second item\",\n      {:nested, [\"Sub-item A\", \"Sub-item B\"]},\n      \"Third item\"\n    ])\n\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.List.render({50, 700}, %{type: :numbered}, [\n      \"Step one\",\n      \"Step two\",\n      \"Step three\"\n    ])","ref":"Pdf.Component.List.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.List.render/4","doc":"Render a list at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.List.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.List.render/4","doc":"- `:type` — `:bullet` (default) or `:numbered`\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — text size (default `10`)\n- `:color` — text color (default dark)\n- `:line_height` — spacing between items (default `16`)\n- `:indent` — indentation per nesting level (default `15`)\n- `:marker_gap` — space between marker and text (default `8`)\n- `:marker_color` — marker color (defaults to `:color`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.List.html#render/4-style-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Items format - Pdf.Component.List.render/4","doc":"Items is a flat list where:\n- `\"string\"` — a list item\n- `{:nested, [items]}` — a nested sub-list","ref":"Pdf.Component.List.html#render/4-items-format"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Metric","doc":"Metric comparison component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a before/after or current vs previous value with delta indicator.\nUseful for reports and dashboards.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Metric.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Metric","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.Metric.render({50, 700}, %{\n      label: \"Revenue\",\n      current: \"$12,450\",\n      previous: \"$10,200\",\n      delta: \"+22%\",\n      delta_direction: :up\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Metric.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Metric.render/3","doc":"Render a metric at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Metric.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Metric.render/3","doc":"- `:label` — metric name\n- `:current` — current/primary value (large)\n- `:previous` — previous value (small, muted)\n- `:delta` — change string (e.g. \"+22%\")\n- `:delta_direction` — `:up`, `:down`, or `:neutral`\n- `:width` — component width (default `200`)\n- `:font` — font name\n- `:background` — optional background color\n- `:border_radius` — corner radius (default `6`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Metric.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.PageHeader","doc":"Automatic page header component for PDF documents.\n\nRegisters a header template that renders on every page using\n`Pdf.on_page(:header, ...)`. Combine with `Pdf.Component.Paginator`\nfor full header + footer support.","ref":"Pdf.Component.PageHeader.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.PageHeader","doc":"doc\n    |> Pdf.Component.PageHeader.apply(%{\n      title: \"Monthly Report\",\n      subtitle: \"Generated by ExPDF\",\n      color: {0.1, 0.1, 0.1}\n    })\n\n    doc\n    |> Pdf.Component.PageHeader.apply(%{\n      left: \"Acme Corp\",\n      right: :date,\n      line: true,\n      line_color: {0.2, 0.5, 0.8}\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.PageHeader.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.PageHeader.apply/2","doc":"Apply an automatic header to the document.\n\nThis registers a header template — all subsequent pages will\nhave the header rendered automatically.","ref":"Pdf.Component.PageHeader.html#apply/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.PageHeader.apply/2","doc":"- `:title` — centered title text\n- `:left` — left-aligned text (overrides centered title)\n- `:right` — right-aligned text, or `:date` for auto date, or `:page` for page number\n- `:subtitle` — smaller text below title (only with `:title`)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — text size (default `9`)\n- `:color` — text color (default dark gray)\n- `:margin_top` — distance from page top (default `30`)\n- `:line` — draw a horizontal line below header (default `true`)\n- `:line_color` — line color (default light gray)\n- `:line_width` — line stroke width (default `0.75`)\n- `:skip_first` — skip header on first page (default `false`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.PageHeader.html#apply/2-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Paginator","doc":"Paginator component for PDF documents.\n\nRegisters a footer template that renders page numbers on every page.\nUses `Pdf.on_page(:footer, ...)` internally.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Paginator.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Paginator","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.Paginator.apply()\n\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Paginator.apply(%{\n      format: :center,\n      font_size: 9,\n      color: {0.5, 0.5, 0.5},\n      prefix: \"Page \"\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Paginator.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Paginator.apply/2","doc":"Apply page numbering to the document.\n\nThis registers a footer template — all subsequent pages will\nhave page numbers rendered automatically.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Paginator.html#apply/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Paginator.apply/2","doc":"- `:format` — `:center` (default), `:right`, or `:left`\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — text size (default `9`)\n- `:color` — text color (default gray)\n- `:margin_bottom` — distance from page bottom (default `30`)\n- `:prefix` — text before number (default `\"Page \"`)\n- `:show_total` — show \"of N\" suffix (default `false`)\n- `:total_pages` — total page count (required if `:show_total` is `true`)\n- `:separator` — separator between number and total (default `\" of \"`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Paginator.html#apply/2-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Progress","doc":"Progress bar component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a horizontal progress/percentage bar with track and fill,\noptional label, and rounded or square ends.\n\nInspired by Material UI's LinearProgress component.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Progress.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Progress","doc":"# Simple progress bar\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Progress.render({50, 400}, %{width: 200, value: 75})\n\n    # Styled progress bar with label\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Progress.render({50, 400}, %{\n      width: 300,\n      value: 42,\n      color: {0.18, 0.72, 0.45},\n      show_label: true,\n      height: 16,\n      border_radius: :rounded\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Progress.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Progress.render/3","doc":"Render a progress bar at `{x, y}` (top-left corner).","ref":"Pdf.Component.Progress.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Progress.render/3","doc":"- `:width` — total bar width (default `200`)\n- `:height` — bar height (default `8`)\n- `:value` — progress percentage 0-100 (default `0`)\n- `:color` — fill color (default blue)\n- `:track_color` — background track color (default light gray)\n- `:border_radius` — `:rounded` (default), `:square`, or number\n- `:show_label` — show percentage text (default `false`)\n- `:label_color` — text color for label (default dark gray)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Progress.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.QrCode","doc":"QR Code PDF component — renders a QR code at a given position.","ref":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage via Builder - Pdf.Component.QrCode","doc":"%{type: :qr, props: %{\n      data: \"https://example.com\",\n      style: %{\n        position: {50, 700},\n        size: 120,\n        ec_level: :h,\n        logo: \"https://example.com/icon.png\",\n        logo_size: 30,\n        label: \"Scan me\"\n      }\n    }}","ref":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.html#module-usage-via-builder"},{"type":"module","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.QrCode","doc":"","ref":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.html#module-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Core - Pdf.Component.QrCode","doc":"- `:data` — the string to encode (required)\n  - `:size` — QR code size in points, square (default `100`)\n  - `:ec_level` — error correction: `:l`, `:m` (default), `:q`, `:h`\n  - `:color` — module (dark) color (default `{0, 0, 0}`)\n  - `:background` — light module color (default `{1, 1, 1}`)\n  - `:quiet_zone` — number of quiet zone modules (default `2`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.html#module-core"},{"type":"module","title":"Border & padding - Pdf.Component.QrCode","doc":"- `:border` — border width (default `0`)\n  - `:border_color` — border stroke color (default `{0.8, 0.8, 0.8}`)\n  - `:border_radius` — corner radius (default `0`)\n  - `:border_fill` — fill color for border area / card background (default `nil`)\n  - `:padding` — extra padding between border and QR (default `0`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.html#module-border-padding"},{"type":"module","title":"Logo / icon overlay (center of QR) - Pdf.Component.QrCode","doc":"- `:logo` — image path, URL, or `{:binary, data}` (default `nil`)\n  - `:logo_size` — logo width & height in points (default 20% of `:size`)\n  - `:logo_background` — background behind logo (default `:background`)\n  - `:logo_padding` — padding around logo image (default `3`)\n  - `:logo_border_radius` — rounded clip for logo area (default `4`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.html#module-logo-icon-overlay-center-of-qr"},{"type":"module","title":"Label - Pdf.Component.QrCode","doc":"- `:label` — text rendered below the QR code (default `nil`)\n  - `:label_font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n  - `:label_font_size` — font size (default `8`)\n  - `:label_color` — text color (default same as `:color`)\n  - `:label_bold` — bold label (default `false`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.html#module-label"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.render/3","doc":"Render a QR code onto the PDF document.\n\n`{x, y}` is the top-left corner. The QR code grows downward.","ref":"Pdf.Component.QrCode.html#render/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Rating","doc":"Rating component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a star/score rating display with filled and empty indicators.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Rating.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Rating","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.Rating.render({50, 700}, %{value: 4, max: 5})\n\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Rating.render({50, 700}, %{\n      value: 3.5,\n      max: 5,\n      filled_color: {0.95, 0.7, 0.0},\n      size: 16\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Rating.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Rating.render/3","doc":"Render a rating at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Rating.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Rating.render/3","doc":"- `:value` — current score (default `0`)\n- `:max` — maximum score (default `5`)\n- `:size` — star size (default `14`)\n- `:filled_color` — filled star color (default gold)\n- `:empty_color` — empty star color (default light gray)\n- `:gap` — space between stars (default `4`)\n- `:show_label` — show \"3.5/5\" text (default `false`)\n- `:label_color` — label text color","ref":"Pdf.Component.Rating.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Signature","doc":"Signature component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a signature line with name, title/role, and optional date.\nUseful for contracts, letters, and formal documents.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Signature.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Signature","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.Signature.render({50, 200}, %{\n      name: \"John Doe\",\n      title: \"CEO, Acme Corp\"\n    })\n\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.Signature.render({50, 200}, %{\n      name: \"Jane Smith\",\n      title: \"Chief Architect\",\n      date: \"May 19, 2026\",\n      width: 250\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.Signature.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Signature.render/3","doc":"Render a signature block at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Signature.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Signature.render/3","doc":"- `:name` — signer name (required)\n- `:title` — role/title below name\n- `:date` — optional date string\n- `:width` — line width (default `200`)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:line_color` — signature line color\n- `:name_color` — name text color\n- `:title_color` — title/date text color\n- `:label` — label above line (e.g. \"Authorized by\")","ref":"Pdf.Component.Signature.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.StatCard","doc":"Stat card component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a dashboard-style KPI card with a large number/value,\na label, and optional trend indicator. Useful for reports and dashboards.","ref":"Pdf.Component.StatCard.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.StatCard","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.StatCard.render({50, 700}, %{\n      value: \"$12,450\",\n      label: \"Monthly Revenue\",\n      width: 150\n    })\n\n    doc |> Pdf.Component.StatCard.render({50, 700}, %{\n      value: \"98.5%\",\n      label: \"Uptime\",\n      trend: \"+2.1%\",\n      trend_color: {0.2, 0.7, 0.3},\n      accent_color: {0.2, 0.5, 0.9}\n    })","ref":"Pdf.Component.StatCard.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.StatCard.render/3","doc":"Render a stat card at `{x, y}` (top-left).","ref":"Pdf.Component.StatCard.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.StatCard.render/3","doc":"- `:value` — the main number/text (required)\n- `:label` — description below the value\n- `:trend` — optional trend string (e.g. \"+5.2%\")\n- `:trend_color` — color for the trend text\n- `:width` — card width (default `150`)\n- `:height` — card height (default `90`)\n- `:background` — card background (default white)\n- `:accent_color` — top accent bar color (default blue)\n- `:value_color` — value text color\n- `:label_color` — label text color\n- `:border_radius` — corner radius (default `6`)\n- `:border` — border width (default `0.5`)\n- `:border_color` — border color","ref":"Pdf.Component.StatCard.html#render/3-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.StepIndicator","doc":"Step indicator component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders numbered steps with a connecting line, showing progress\nthrough a multi-step process (wizard-style).","ref":"Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.StepIndicator","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.render({50, 700}, %{width: 450}, [\n      %{label: \"Account\", status: :completed},\n      %{label: \"Profile\", status: :active},\n      %{label: \"Review\", status: :pending},\n      %{label: \"Done\", status: :pending}\n    ])","ref":"Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.render/4","doc":"Render a step indicator at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.render/4","doc":"- `:width` — total width (default `400`)\n- `:step_size` — circle diameter (default `24`)\n- `:completed_color` — completed step color\n- `:active_color` — active step color\n- `:pending_color` — pending step color\n- `:font` — font name","ref":"Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.html#render/4-style-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Steps format - Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.render/4","doc":"List of maps: `%{label: \"Step name\", status: :completed | :active | :pending}`","ref":"Pdf.Component.StepIndicator.html#render/4-steps-format"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.TOC","doc":"Table of Contents component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a list of entries with titles, optional dot leaders,\nand right-aligned page numbers.","ref":"Pdf.Component.TOC.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.TOC","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.TOC.render({50, 700}, %{width: 450}, [\n      %{title: \"Introduction\", page: 1},\n      %{title: \"Getting Started\", page: 3, level: 1},\n      %{title: \"Installation\", page: 3, level: 2},\n      %{title: \"Configuration\", page: 5, level: 2},\n      %{title: \"Advanced Usage\", page: 10, level: 1}\n    ])","ref":"Pdf.Component.TOC.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.TOC.render/4","doc":"Render a table of contents at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.TOC.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.TOC.render/4","doc":"- `:width` — total width (default `450`)\n- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — base text size (default `10`)\n- `:color` — title text color\n- `:page_color` — page number color\n- `:dot_color` — dot leader color\n- `:line_height` — row spacing (default `18`)\n- `:indent` — indentation per level (default `20`)\n- `:dots` — show dot leaders (default `true`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.TOC.html#render/4-style-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Entries format - Pdf.Component.TOC.render/4","doc":"List of maps: `%{title: \"Section\", page: 1, level: 1}`\nLevel defaults to `1`. Level `0` renders bold (chapter heading).","ref":"Pdf.Component.TOC.html#render/4-entries-format"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Timeline","doc":"Timeline component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a vertical timeline with dots, connecting line, and event entries.\nUseful for CVs, project history, and changelogs.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Timeline.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Component.Timeline","doc":"doc |> Pdf.Component.Timeline.render({50, 700}, %{}, [\n      %{date: \"2026\", title: \"Launch\", description: \"Product released\"},\n      %{date: \"2025\", title: \"Beta\", description: \"Beta testing phase\"},\n      %{date: \"2024\", title: \"Founded\", description: \"Company started\"}\n    ])","ref":"Pdf.Component.Timeline.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Timeline.render/4","doc":"Render a timeline at `{x, y}`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Timeline.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Timeline.render/4","doc":"- `:font` — font name (default `\"Helvetica\"`)\n- `:font_size` — text size (default `10`)\n- `:color` — title/description color\n- `:date_color` — date text color\n- `:line_color` — vertical line color\n- `:dot_color` — dot fill color\n- `:dot_size` — dot diameter (default `6`)\n- `:row_height` — height per entry (default `50`)\n- `:date_width` — width reserved for dates (default `60`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Timeline.html#render/4-style-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Events format - Pdf.Component.Timeline.render/4","doc":"List of maps: `%{date: \"2026\", title: \"Event\", description: \"Details\"}`","ref":"Pdf.Component.Timeline.html#render/4-events-format"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.StyledTable","doc":"Styled table component with CSS-like configuration.\n\nRenders data tables with customizable borders, rounded corners, backgrounds,\npadding, and per-row/cell styling using `Pdf.Style` maps.","ref":"Pdf.StyledTable.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Pdf.StyledTable","doc":"Pdf.StyledTable.render(doc, [\n      [\"Name\", \"Qty\", \"Price\"],\n      [\"Widget A\", \"5\", \"$10.00\"],\n      [\"Widget B\", \"3\", \"$15.00\"]\n    ], %{\n      columns: [\n        %{width: 200},\n        %{width: 80, align: :center},\n        %{width: 120, align: :right}\n      ],\n      header: %{bold: true, background: {0.2, 0.3, 0.5}, color: :white, padding: 8},\n      row: %{padding: 6, border_bottom: 1},\n      alt_row: %{background: {0.95, 0.95, 1.0}},\n      border: 1,\n      border_color: {0.3, 0.3, 0.3},\n      border_radius: 6\n    })","ref":"Pdf.StyledTable.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.StyledTable.render/3","doc":"Render a styled table on the document at the current cursor position.\n\nReturns the updated document with cursor moved below the table.","ref":"Pdf.StyledTable.html#render/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Pdf.StyledTable.render/3","doc":"- `:columns` — list of column config maps: `%{width: n, align: :left|:center|:right, style: %{}}`\n- `:header` — style map for header row (first row of data), or `nil` to treat all rows as body\n- `:row` — default style map for body rows\n- `:alt_row` — style map merged into every other body row (zebra stripes)\n- `:footer` — style map for the last row\n- `:border` — outer border width (number)\n- `:border_color` — outer border color\n- `:border_radius` — corner radius for outer border\n- `:background` — default cell background\n- `:padding` — default cell padding (CSS shorthand)\n- `:font`, `:font_size`, `:color` — default text styling\n- `:line_height` — height per text line in points","ref":"Pdf.StyledTable.html#render/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.StyledTable.render_on_page/4","doc":"Render a styled table on a Page struct (low-level).","ref":"Pdf.StyledTable.html#render_on_page/4"},{"type":"extras","title":"ExPdfComponents","doc":"# ExPdfComponents\n\n[![Hex.pm](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/v/ex_pdf_components.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf_components)\n[![Docs](https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-hexdocs-blue)](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_pdf_components)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/l/ex_pdf_components.svg)](https://github.com/MisaelMa/ExPDF/blob/main/LICENSE.md)\n\nReusable PDF components and a declarative template builder for Elixir.\nBuilt on top of [`ex_pdf_core`](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf_core).\n\nPart of the [ExPDF](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf) umbrella.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - ExPdfComponents","doc":"```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:ex_pdf_components, \"~> 1.0\"}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\n> Most users should depend on [`ex_pdf`](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf)\n> instead, which bundles core, components, and the reader.","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Components - ExPdfComponents","doc":"| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `Pdf.Builder` | Declarative template engine with cursor layout and auto-pagination |\n| `Pdf.StyledTable` | Data tables with headers, styles, and column config |\n| `Pdf.Component.Alert` | Alert/notification boxes |\n| `Pdf.Component.Avatar` | Circular/rounded image avatars |\n| `Pdf.Component.Badge` | Inline text badges |\n| `Pdf.Component.Barcode` | Code 128 barcodes (via `ex_barcode`) |\n| `Pdf.Component.Blockquote` | Styled quotation blocks |\n| `Pdf.Component.Card` | Container with shadow, border, background |\n| `Pdf.Component.Chart` | Basic chart rendering |\n| `Pdf.Component.Chip` | Tag/chip labels |\n| `Pdf.Component.CodeBlock` | Monospaced code blocks |\n| `Pdf.Component.Divider` | Horizontal rule / separator |\n| `Pdf.Component.Footnote` | Page footnotes |\n| `Pdf.Component.KeyValue` | Label–value pair lists |\n| `Pdf.Component.List` | Ordered/unordered lists |\n| `Pdf.Component.Metric` | KPI / metric display |\n| `Pdf.Component.PageHeader` | Page header with title and subtitle |\n| `Pdf.Component.Paginator` | Page number footer |\n| `Pdf.Component.Progress` | Progress bar |\n| `Pdf.Component.QrCode` | QR codes (via `ex_qr`) |\n| `Pdf.Component.Rating` | Star ratings |\n| `Pdf.Component.Signature` | Signature block |\n| `Pdf.Component.StatCard` | Statistics card |\n| `Pdf.Component.StepIndicator` | Step/wizard indicator |\n| `Pdf.Component.Timeline` | Timeline visualization |\n| `Pdf.Component.Toc` | Table of contents |","ref":"readme.html#components"},{"type":"extras","title":"Builder example - ExPdfComponents","doc":"```elixir\ntemplate = [\n  %{type: :row, props: %{\n    children: [\n      {3, [%{type: :text, props: %{content: \"Title\", style: %{position: {0, -16}}}}]},\n      {1, [%{type: :text, props: %{content: \"Brand\", style: %{position: {0, -16}}}}]}\n    ],\n    style: %{position: :cursor, size: {:full, 30}}\n  }},\n  %{type: :spacer, props: %{amount: 10}}\n]\n\nPdf.Builder.render(template, config)\n```\n\nThe Builder supports cursor-based layout with automatic pagination — when\ncontent overflows the page, page breaks are inserted automatically.","ref":"readme.html#builder-example"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - ExPdfComponents","doc":"MIT. See [LICENSE.md](https://github.com/MisaelMa/ExPDF/blob/main/LICENSE.md).","ref":"readme.html#license"}],"proglang":"elixir","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.2"},"content_type":"text/markdown"}